      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYWYN'S KING (6) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Faded to finish fourth over 457m at Q Lakeside (26.04) in a Grade 5 but is better placed coming back in trip. Form at the trip excellent including three wins. Has good speed so he should be prominent despite the draw. Has ability and is a key runner. BELLA GEORGIA (1) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at this track, but was among the placings at Capalaba three back. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Has the ability and can find best this time. SARILDA (8) boasts a strong record this journey with six wins and three minors from 17 tries. In the money last time at this track (16.68) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2.25 lengths third. Looks one of the chances. BROWNLOW (4) is one of the chances after collecting a minor prize last time.",
